<episodedetails><title>City States and Civilisations</title><plot>In this  episode, we see how city states and kingdoms gave rise to rich and diverse civilisations, including some of the most iconic works of art on the continent: the Benin bronzes, dating back to the 13th century.

Zeinab Badawi travels to Nigeria where she is granted a rare interview with the  King of the Benin kingdom in southern Nigeria. She meets the Queen Mother of Lagos, at her ancestral palace on Lagos Island where she relates the history of the Yoruba people.</plot></episodedetails>